      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Leafs",
        "body": "The Toronto Maple Leafs' season ended not with a bang but with a whimper - a seven-game losing streak that sealed what's been a season of unfulfilled promise and hard questions. <strong>The Leafs finished 32-36-14, eighth in the Atlantic Division with 78 points, 31 games behind the pace setter, their playoff hopes extinguished before May arrived.</strong> This isn't the collapse of a contender; it's the slow fade of a team that never quite found its footing, caught between ambition and execution.\n\nThe math was always going to be brutal. Seventy-eight points doesn't get you to October in this league - it gets you to the lottery. The Leafs limped across the finish line, and now comes the reckoning: Does this core stay intact? Does the front office pull the trigger on coaching changes? The draft lottery looms, and with it, the chance to reset. <strong>Watch for moves in the coming weeks - the free agency period will tell you whether management believes in salvaging this core or building something new from the rubble.</strong> For now, the Leafs have nothing but time and hard truths.",
        "updated": "Updated May 2, 2026"
      },
