      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Commanders",
        "body": "The draft dust settles in D.C., and the Commanders - fresh off a 5-12 slog that left them third in the NFC East, six games back - emerged with an <strong>A-minus haul headlined by Ohio State's Sonny Styles at No. 7 overall</strong>, a rare linebacker gem whose 43½-inch vertical and 4.46 forty scream immediate defensive salvation for Dan Quinn's revamped unit. Styles, with his 85.0-plus grades against the run and pass, slots right into a linebacker room begging for disruption - Quinn's already floating the green dot for him as a rookie signal-caller, no small ask after last year's 31st-ranked EPA defense imploded. Middle rounds delivered steals like Tennessee edge Joshua Josephs (Pick 147, 87.1 PFF grade, No. 63 board rank) for rotation juice, Penn State's Kaytron Allen (Pick 187, 89.5 grade) to spell the backfield, Michigan State's Matt Gulbin at center (Pick 209), and Rutgers QB Athan Kaliakmanis (Pick 223) as developmental insurance. Undrafted free agents are trickling in for depth, but this class - top-ranked in average WAA added at 0.31 - fits Quinn's scheme like a glove, injecting athleticism and high-floor producers. <strong>Watch Styles in OTAs; if he grabs that green dot, Washington's rookie revolution starts now.</strong>",
        "updated": "Updated May 2, 2026"
      },
